<seg id="2081">In & quantaplus, there are some key concepts. in order to understand these concepts and to take full advantage of them, one must first acquaint themselves with these fundamental concepts.</seg>
<seg id="2082">In & quantaplus, the working area is divided into three areas: global, local and project-related. this distinction concerns a number of components in & quantaplus.</seg>
<seg id="2083">Global elements are available for everyone who uses & quantaplus. from toolbars to actions everything that is marked globally is stored in the common folder structure of & quantaplus. this allows the group of administrators to secure various toolbars, actions and patterns in the global tree, which are then available to everyone in a multi-user environment.</seg>
<seg id="2084">Local elements represent a personal collection of web development resources for a single user. these are user-specific patterns and toolbars. local elements are stored in the user directory, so that only this user can use them personally.</seg>
<seg id="2085">Project-related elements are available only within a particular project. this can be everything from & CSS; patterns to toolbars with special actions especially for the files of a particular project. simply put, this is the most restricted size. all elements are stored in the folder tree of the project, making the common use of special tools and patterns emitted by all employees within the project.</seg>
